class Solution {
    public String reverseParentheses(String s) {
        java.util.Stack<StringBuilder> stack = new java.util.Stack<>();
        StringBuilder res = new StringBuilder();
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '(') {
                stack.push(res);
                res = new StringBuilder();
            } else if (c == ')') {
                res.reverse();
                res = stack.pop().append(res);
            } else {
                res.append(c);
            }
        }
        return res.toString();
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Utilizes a stack to track and reverse substrings within parentheses, efficiently handling nested cases by reversing the innermost parentheses first.
